    dc:description "FIG. 5. — Hyaenodonta from Fort Ternan: A-I, Dissopsalis cf. pyroclasticus; A-C, KNM-FT 15092, left M1 in buccal (A), lingual (B), occlusal (C) views; D, E, KNM-FT 13771,right m2 in buccal (D), lingual (E), and occlusal (F) views; G-I, KNM-FT 13770, right m3 in buccal (G), lingual (H), and occlusal (I) views; J, Hyainailourinae gen.et sp. indet., KNM-FT 3359,left upper canine in medial view. Scale bars: A-I, 20 mm; J, 100 mm." ;
